      "id": 358243,
      "is_answer_order_important": false,
      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>Diethylstilbestrol (DES) has estrogenic activity even though it is structurally unrelated to steroids. Once used as an additive in animal feed, DES has been implicated as a causative agent in several types of cancer. Show how DES can be drawn so that it is sterically similar to estradiol.</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBbTRZIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--12bd4be4bb0a96549a4750f827ebf8ce8f86b5fd/OChem_27_EC_019.jpg\" alt=\"The structures of diethylstilbestrol and estradiol. Diethylstilbestrol is a diethyl subsituted diphenol. Estradiol is an aromatic steroid with a phenol and wedged methyl and hydroxyl groups. \">",
